version: 1
display_name: PHTN-50-000040 - The Photon operating system must not have the telnet package installed.
global_description: |-
  Passwords need to be protected at all times, and encryption is the standard method for protecting passwords. If passwords are not encrypted, they can be plainly read (i.e., clear text) and easily compromised.
osfinger:
  - VMware Photon OS-5
refs:
  disa_stig:
    - PHTN-50-000040
  srg:
    - SRG-OS-000074-GPOS-00042
  cci:
    - CCI-000197
  nist:
    - IA-5 (1) (c)
benchmark_id:
  vcf9_photon_5:
    type: custom
    desc: The Photon operating system must not have the telnet package installed.
    control_id: PHTN-50-000040
    scored: true
    profile:
      - default
    information: |-
      At the command line, run the following command to verify telnet is not installed:

      # rpm -qa | grep telnet

      If any results are returned indicating telnet is installed, this is a finding.
    rationale: |-
      Passwords need to be protected at all times, and encryption is the standard method for protecting passwords. If passwords are not encrypted, they can be plainly read (i.e., clear text) and easily compromised.
    remediation: |-
      At the command line, run the following command:

      # tdnf remove <package name>
